<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 4:07PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Henry and southeastern Franklin Counties through 445 PM
EDT...
At 407 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ferrum, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sydnorsville...
Ferrum...
Snow Creek...
Leatherwood...
Oak Level...
Sontag...
and Figsboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
